{{Infobox_OS | name = Linux Deepin | screenshot = [[Image:Hiweed_Screenshot.png|250px]] | caption = Linux Deepin | website = [http://linuxdeepin.com/ linuxdeepin.com] | family = [[Linux]] | source_model = [[Open source]] | latest_release_version = 10.12 | latest_release_date = 2010-12-31 | latest_preview_version = 10.12 Beta | latest_preview_date = 2010-11-30 | language = [[Chinese language|Chinese]] with [[English language|English]] | kernel_type = [[Monolithic kernel]] | ui = [[GNOME]](01â0.7), [[Xfce|XDE]] (0.8â2.0), [[LXDE]] (9.12) | license = GPL and others }} '''Linux Deepin''' is a [[Linux distribution]] based on [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]]. It is tailored for [[Chinese language]] users and includes preconfigured Chinese applications such as simplified Chinese input methods, [[Chinese dictionaries]], and Chinese [[TrueType]] [[fonts]].
Linux Deepin 10.12 features [[Linux Mint]] menu and the [[Mac OS X]]-like [[Cairo-Dock]] panel for application launch, as well as a Chinese input method [[Yong]], [[Yozo Office]] 2009 SP1 and a space-saving "global menu" in the top panel.<ref>[http://linux.deepin.org/10.12 Linux Deepin 10.12 Release Notes]</ref>
The project was originally called '''Hiweed Linux'''.
